title: Lee Enterprises (LEE) Earning Somewhat Favorable News Coverage, Accern Reports
content: Media coverage about Lee Enterprises (NYSE:LEE) has been trending somewhat positive on Saturday, Accern Sentiment Analysis reports. Accern identifies negative and positive press coverage by monitoring more than twenty million news and blog sources in real time. Accern ranks coverage of public companies on a scale of -1 to 1, with scores closest to one being the most favorable. Lee Enterprises earned a news sentiment score of 0.07 on Accern’s scale. Accern also gave news headlines about the company an impact score of 47.7559581810871 out of 100, indicating that recent press coverage is somewhat unlikely to have an impact on the stock’s share price in the next several days.    Here are some of the headlines that may have impacted Accern’s rankings:    Software-based networks lay foundation of networking’s future (searchsdn.techtarget.com)  Dragos’ Robert Lee discusses latest ICS threats, hacking back (searchsecurity.techtarget.com)  Option Care Nurses Earn Elite Certified Registered Nurse Infusion (CRNI®) Credential (scnow.com)  Newport News to host ‘Meet and Greet’ with new police chief Wednesday (dailypress.com)  Quadratic Voting: A New Way to Govern Blockchains for Enterprises (forbes.com)    Separately, Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Lee Enterprises from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Saturday, February 3rd.    LEE traded up $0.15 on Friday, hitting $2.70. 158,653 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged, compared to its average volume of 159,259. Lee Enterprises has a fifty-two week low of $1.75 and a fifty-two week high of $2.75. The company has a quick ratio of 0.65, a current ratio of 0.69 and a debt-to-equity ratio of -8.72. The stock has a market cap of $145.45 million, a PE ratio of 8.71 and a beta of 2.17.    Lee Enterprises (NYSE:LEE) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, May 3rd. The company reported $0.03 EPS for the quarter. Lee Enterprises had a negative return on equity of 24.72% and a net margin of 8.42%. The business had revenue of $127.81 million for the quarter.    About Lee Enterprises    Lee Enterprises, Incorporated provides local news and information, and advertising services primarily in the Midwest, Mountain West, and West regions of the United States. It publishes 47 daily newspapers with 0.8 million circulation units, as well as Sunday newspapers with 1.2 million circulation units; and 300 weekly newspapers, and classified and niche publications in 22 states with print and related digital operations.
